<font color="#FF0000">DECORATIONS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 20  6:35:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
Don't worry about displaying your medals. <br><br>
Keeping them in the dresser drawer, in my opinion, is the same as saying that you were never there. I remember several times, many years ago, failing to admit that I was A Vietnam Vet. We all know the feeling.<br><br>
Always in the back of my mind, when ever I think of my own awards, is the terrible human price that the participants (military and civilian) had to pay in Vietnam in order for us to &quot;prove ourselves&quot;. A sobering thought isn't it? <br><br>
We are aware of our failings in Vietnam. We admit to them even. <br><br>
Now is the time to show that there was goodness and heroism there also. <br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


